tplinkProtocolVlanMIB.name: tplinkProtocolVlanMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

tplinkProtocolVlanMIB.description: Protocol VLAN (Virtual Local Area Network) is the way to classify VLANs based on Protocols. A Protocol is relative to a single VLAN ID. The untagged packets and the priority-tagged packets matching the protocol template will be tagged with this VLAN ID.

protocolTemplateTable.name: protocolTemplateTable
protocolTemplateTable.description: The Protocol Template should be created before configuring the Protocol VLAN. By default, the switch has defined the IP Template, ARP Template, RARP Template, etc. You can add more Protocol Template.

templateEntry.name: templateEntry
templateEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of a protocol template.

templateProtocolName.name: templateProtocolName
templateProtocolName.description: Give a name for the Protocol Template,1-8 characters

templateEtherType.name: templateEtherType
templateEtherType.description: Enter the Ethernet protocol type field in the protocol template, for example 0800,0ff0. The value is [dsap ssap] when frame type is llc.

templateStatus.name: templateStatus
templateStatus.description: the following two values are states: these values may be read or written active(1), the following three values are actions: these values may be written, but are never read createAndGo(4), destroy(6)

protocolGroupTable.name: protocolGroupTable
protocolGroupTable.description: Here you can configure the Protocol VLAN.

protocolVlanEntry.name: protocolVlanEntry
protocolVlanEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of a protocol vlan.

protocolName.name: protocolName
protocolName.description: Displays the protocol template name of the VLAN.

protocolVlanId.name: protocolVlanId
protocolVlanId.description: Enter the ID number of the Protocol VLAN. This VLAN should be one of the 802.1Q VLANs the ingress port belongs to,1-4094.

protocolVlanStatus.name: protocolVlanStatus
protocolVlanStatus.description: the following two values are states: these values may be read or written active(1), the following three values are actions: these values may be written, but are never read createAndGo(4), destroy(6)
